<h2 id="kirill-gorin">Kirill Gorin</h2>

<p>They use Rails (surprisingly for me) in Coub. They don&rsquo;t use carrierwave and are not afraid of reinventing the wheel. Attachments are a corner stone of thier service. They process millions of files every day, with different codecs and resolutions, images and sounds. So they need thier own infrastructure for storing and processing attachments.</p>

<h2 id="group-discussion">Group discussion</h2>

<p>Where to store business logic? Guys tried to joke, becuase there is no ultimate solution actually. If you write an app with complex business logic you shouldn&rsquo;t use Rails or at least activerecord. Good news is that Rails team started working on activeform. Community moves slowly towards service objects, forms and PORO.
</p>

