<h2 id="sandi-metz">Sandi Metz</h2>

<p>She couldn&rsquo;t come to Russia, so talk was online instead. We looked at Sandi&rsquo;s face on a big screen, while she was in her small office with bookshelves on the background. I guess she&rsquo;s spent a lot of time prepearing to this talk, because handreds of steps of a refactoring from the beginning to the end were shown.</p>

<p>Make things simple. Don&rsquo;t be afraid of code duplication, because wrong abstraction is even worse. You must have tests before refactoring started. You must have your tests green. If you don&rsquo;t understand business logic, trust existing tests and try to do your best.</p>

